<TEI.2><text><body><div1 type="alphabetic letter" n="I" org="uniform" sample="complete"><entryFree key="Innocence" type="main" opt="n"><orth extent="full" opt="n">Innocence,</orth> 1) freedom from a particular guilt, guiltlessness: <bibl n="shak. wt 3.2.31" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. III, 2, 31</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r2 1.3.84" default="NO" valid="yes">R2 I, 3, 84</bibl> (M. Edd. <emph>innocency</emph>). <bibl n="shak. 2h4 4.1.45" default="NO" valid="yes">H4B IV, 1, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 2.3.106" default="NO" valid="yes">H6B II, 3, 106</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. 2h6 4.4.59" default="NO" valid="yes">IV, 4, 59</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 20</bibl> (Ff Q<hi rend="sub">2. <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 20</bibl> <bibl n="shak. r3 3.5.20" default="NO" valid="yes">R3 III, 5, 20</bibl> 5</hi> <emph>innocency</emph>). <bibl n="shak. h8 1.1.208" default="NO" valid="yes">H8 I, 1, 208</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 3.2.301" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 301</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. h8 5.1.142" default="NO" valid="yes">V, 1, 142</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tit 1.437" default="NO" valid="yes">Tit. I, 437</bibl>.<lb />2) freedom from any thought of evil, harmlessness, purity and simplicity of heart: <bibl n="shak. luc 1341" default="NO" valid="yes">Lucr. 1341</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tmp 3.1.82" default="NO" valid="yes">Tp. III, 1, 82</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 2.2.45" default="NO" valid="yes">Mids. II, 2, 45</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mnd 3.2.202" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 2, 202</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 145</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 2.4.48" default="NO" valid="yes">Tw. II, 4, 48</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tn 3.1.169" default="NO" valid="yes">III, 1, 169</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 1.2.69" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. I, 2, 69</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. wt 2.2.41" default="NO" valid="yes">II, 2, 41</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. jn 4.1.64" default="NO" valid="yes">John IV, 1, 64</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. tim 1.1.199" default="NO" valid="yes">Tim. I, 1, 199</bibl>. <bibl n="shak. per 1.2.93" default="NO" valid="yes">Per. I, 2, 93</bibl>.
<lb />3) plainness and artlessness bordering on silliness: <cit><quote>who has not only his i., which is much, to excuse him,</quote> <bibl n="shak. wt 5.2.70" default="NO" valid="yes">Wint. V, 2, 70</bibl></cit>. Perhaps also in <bibl n="shak. mv 1.1.145" default="NO" valid="yes">Merch. I, 1, 145</bibl>.
</entryFree></div1></body></text></TEI.2>